Page.create!(
  name: 'The project',
  language: 'en',
  category: 'about',
  slug: 'the-project',
  content: <<~PROJECT
    <h1>The project</h1>
    <h2>Impact of plastic pollution</h2>
    <p><span style="font-size: 14px;">8 millions tons of plastics are dumped into the oceans each year. Damage to residents, endocrine disruptors, injuries, death of marine animals by ingestion or strangulation, these massive pollution causes major economic losses (decline of tourism, impacts on fishing ...).</span></p>
    <p><span style="font-size: 14px;">80% of the waste found on the coast comes from the mainland by rivers, rainwater. The rest comes from maritime traffic and offshore activities. An estimated 10,000 containers are lost at sea each year worldwide.</span></p>
    <p><span style="font-size: 14px;">Economic loss (tourism decline), damage to marine habitats, injury or death of marine animals by ingestion or strangulation. Navigation issues, displacement of marine species that clings to waste (<a href="http://www.marinedebris.noaa.gov" rel="noopener noreferrer" target="_blank">www.marinedebris.noaa.gov</a>).</span></p>
    <h2>Tracker's role</h2>
    <p><span style="font-size: 14px;">Among plastic pollution, some waste tell a story. Thoses trackers allows to qualify and quantify pollution coming from lost in sea containers or dumping. With more than 150 daily cargo ships passing off the french coast, the altantic coast is an unique observatory for tracker.</span></p>
    <p><span style="font-size: 14px;">Tracers are chosen in a collaborative way between the associations and the </span><a href="https://www.facebook.com/groups/279818875502438" rel="noopener noreferrer" target="_blank"><span style="font-size: 14px;">observation network</span></a><span style="font-size: 14px;">, according to some criteria (quantity found, localization of the reports, ...). Some tracers such as MacKesson syringes, Pullman slippers, Zp caps or HP printer cartridges come from containers dropped at sea. Other tracers have completely different origins such as lobster traps that come from North America. North or Pascual yogurt pots that come from Spanish ships. The list of tracers is evolutionary, which makes it possible to add new tracers in case of new discoveries. This was particularly the case in January 2018 with milk powder pots and their plastic pods following a loss of containers off Galicia.</span></p>
    <h2>The impact of plastic pollution</h2>
    <p>
        <span style="font-size: 14px;"><span title=""><br>8 millions tons of plastics are dumped into the oceans each year.</span> <span title="">Damage to residents, endocrine disruptors, injuries, death of marine animals by ingestion or strangulation, these massive pollution causes major economic losses (decline of tourism, impacts on fisheries ...).</span>
        <br>
        <br><span title="">80% of the waste found on the coast comes from the mainland by rivers, rainwater.</span> <span title="">The rest comes from maritime traffic and offshore activities. An estimated 10,000 containers are lost at sea each year worldwide.</span>
        <br>
        <br><span title="">Economic loss (tourism decline), damage to marine habitats, injury or death of marine animals by ingestion or strangulation.</span> <span contenteditable="false" tabindex="-1" title="">Problems for navigation, displacement of marine species that clings to waste</span>
        <br>
        </span>
    </p>
PROJECT
